The paper proposes a neural network-based approach for named entity recognition (NER) that uses automatically learned features only. This falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP), which is typically classified under cs.CL. The paper also extensively discusses the use of deep learning techniques, which is a common theme in the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper focuses on improving the performance of NER, which is a specific task within NLP, and this could potentially fall under the sub-category of natural language understanding (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the use of embeddings, which is a common technique in information retrieval (cs.IR).
